parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the rear liftgate panel can cause the glass to shatter, leading to injury or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Cracking of the rear liftgate panel
often near the Ford emblem
vertical crack from the rear window to the bottom of the liftgate
crack appears suddenly
and the glass may shatter when closing the liftgate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling and rusting of the paint can lead to water leakage and damage to the vehicle's body.
symptoms: Peeling paint on the roof and hood
rusting on the roof
bubbling of paint in roof channels
and rusting of the body.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rotting of the frame and weld failure can cause the entire hub/axle/wheel assembly to rip off the vehicle, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Frame rotting along the welds
lengthwise running with the frame
and weld failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire can cause accidents, damage to the vehicle, and injury to occupants.
symptoms: Tire came apart
causing damage to the vehicle's body
and the driver's side headlight
blinker
and molding were damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The transmission warning light flashes
the vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle slips or hesitates when accelerating
the vehicle will not shift into gear
the vehicle shuts off while driving
the transmission makes abnormal noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shifter can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The gear shifter breaks off
the gear shifter lever becomes stuck
the gear shifter will not move out of park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning fuel gauge can cause the driver to be unaware of the actual fuel level, leading to unexpected fuel exhaustion, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reads empty or erratic
the service engine soon light is illuminated
and the fuel level sensor is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty fuel pump and sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to unexpected fuel exhaustion, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reads empty or erratic
the service engine soon light is illuminated
and the fuel pump and sensor need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Filler Neck and Tank Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty fuel filler neck and tank can cause fuel to spill out during refueling, leading to a fire hazard and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel spills out during refueling
the fuel filler neck is damaged
and the fuel tank needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty fuel cap sensor can cause the check fuel cap light to illuminate, leading to unnecessary repairs and inconvenience.
symptoms: The check fuel cap light is illuminated
the fuel cap needs to be replaced
and the fuel system needs to be inspected.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty fuel system can cause the engine to stall and lose power, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the service engine soon light is illuminated
and the fuel system needs to be inspected.
